    "betterquesting:10": {
      "autoClaim:1": 0,
      "desc:8": "You can find amethyst blocks, crystals, and calcite blocks in underground geodes. \n\nDuring the Steam Age, calcite blocks become incredibly useful because you can put them into a Forge Hammer to obtain valuable calcite dust, which is used for crafting the Bricked Blast Furnace. They can usually be found between Y-levels 5 and 46.\n\nAmethyst can also be mined and used as a source of silicon dioxide. One amethyst block drops 9 amethyst dust, making it a great option for obtaining silicon dioxide.\n[note]\nYou can use an Ore Finder with calcite dust inserted into it to locate calcite deposits more easily.\n[/note]",
